-- Moody's Puts Hongkong & Shanghai Bank, Hang Seng on Review for Rating Bump
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-10-08T12:39:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-08/moody-s-puts-hongkong-shanghai-bank-hang-seng-bank-on-review.html
Moody’s Investors Service said it put
the Aa2 long-term foreign currency deposit ratings of  Hongkong &
Shanghai Banking Corp.  and  Hang Seng Bank Ltd . on review for a
possible upgrade.  The review follows the announcement that Moody’s put Hong
Kong’s Aa2 government bond ratings on review for a possible
upgrade. The ratings of Hongkong & Shanghai Banking and Hang
Seng are now constrained by Hong Kong’s ceiling, Moody’s said in
an e-mailed statement today.  The ratings company also put Hong Kong Mortgage Corp.’s Aa2
long-term local and foreign currency senior unsecured debt and
issuer ratings on review for a possible upgrade.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Joshua Fellman  at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  